article.description: — Jamal Cain scored 17 points and Jalen Moore had 16 points, nine assists and seven rebounds as Oakland defeated IUPUI 69-58 in the first round of the Horizon League tournament on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Oakland tops short-handed IUPUI 69-58 in Horizon tourney
article.linkText: Oakland tops short-handed IUPUI 69-58 in Horizon tourney
article.story: OAKLAND, Mich. -- — Jamal Cain scored 17 points and Jalen Moore had 16 points, nine assists and seven rebounds as Oakland defeated IUPUI 69-58 in the first round of the Horizon League tournament on Tuesday night. Blake Lampman had 14 points for Oakland (20-11). B.J. Maxwell had 15 points for the Jaguars (3-26). Boston Stanton III added 13 points. Nathan McClure had 12 points and eight rebounds. IUPUI only had five players available for the game. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
